use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 27, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zrw1665702750469.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zrw1665702750469.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zrw1665702750469.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zrw1665702750469\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">During the construction phase of application development activity, you create development objects that define the application components and runtime libraries needed for the application. Application components can reuse definitions that you created in the modeling phase.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__context_w3007ab1b5b1_w3008ab1b5_w3009ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__p_d10832e1_d10833e1_d10834e1\">The high-level process for constructing application\n            components is as follows:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__li_d5003e1_d5004e1_d5005e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__p_d10835e1_d10836e1_d10837e1\">Create the required components.\n Uniface has different types of components suited to different purposes, such as Server Pages and Forms for the user interface and Services for business logic.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__li_d5006e1_d5007e1_d5008e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__p_d10838e1_d10839e1_d10840e1\">For each component, define its data structure.\n               This controls the data (component entities and fields) used in the component, the\n               order in which data is processed, and the default behavior when it is stored or\n               deleted. In most cases, component entities are created by inserting modeled entities.\n               You can also create non-modeled component entities that are specific to the\n               component. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zii1704964501123.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zii1704964501123.html\" title=\"For services and server pages, use the Define Structure worksheet to add and organize entities and fields in the component structure.\">Define the Component Structure</a>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__li_d5009e1_d5010e1_d5011e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Write script modules that control component-specific behavior. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gtm1665702624482.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gtm1665702624482.html\" title=\"A script module is a named collection of ProcScript belonging to a development object. Script modules are analogous to events and methods in other programming languages.\">Script Modules</a>.\n        </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__li_d5012e1_d5013e1_d5014e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">For presentation components, design the layout and appearance of the component. For server pages, this is done using HTML.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__li_d5015e1_d5016e1_d5017e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create global objects that components can access at runtime, such as messages,\n               variables, and global ProcScript functions. Global objects are defined and deployed\n               in libraries. </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__result_w3010ab1b5b5_w3011ab1b5_w3012ab1\">The information in\n         this section is applicable for all types of applications and components. Detailed\n         information on developing specific types of applications is available in other sections.\n         For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nvu1665702750539.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nvu1665702750539.html\" title=\"You can use Uniface to develop, test, and deploy web-based applications. Web applications have unique requirements with regard to testing and deployment, state management and authentication, data maintenance, and security.\">Developing Web Applications</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"shh1665702750613.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/shh1665702750613.html\" title=\"Enterprise desktop applications are distributed client/server applications—they allow users to retrieve and maintain data in a remote database using a locally-run application. Desktop applications are usually highly interactive, and provide a much faster response time than most web applications.\">Developing Desktop Applications</a>. <div class=\"sectiondiv\">\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://learn.rocketsoftware.com/course/view.php?id=44\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Learn More\" class=\"image\" id=\"zrw1665702750469__image_ftc_rh4_vdc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/My_Learn_More_Button.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/></a></p>\n</div></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nvu1665702750539.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Developing Web Applications</a><p>You can use Uniface to develop, test, and deploy web-based applications. Web applications have unique requirements with regard to testing and deployment, state management and authentication, data maintenance, and security.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/shh1665702750613.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Developing Desktop Applications</a><p>Enterprise desktop applications are distributed client/server applications—they allow users to retrieve and maintain data in a remote database using a locally-run application. Desktop applications are usually highly interactive, and provide a much faster response time than most web applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617456\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617456\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Constructing Components and Other Objects Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 During the construction phase of application development activity, you create development objects that define the application components and runtime libraries needed for the application. Application components can reuse definitions that you created in the modeling phase. The high-level process for constructing application components is as follows: Create the required components. Uniface has different types of components suited to different purposes, such as Server Pages and Forms for the user interface and Services for business logic. For each component, define its data structure. This controls the data (component entities and fields) used in the component, the order in which data is processed, and the default behavior when it is stored or deleted. In most cases, component entities are created by inserting modeled entities. You can also create non-modeled component entities that are specific to the component. For more information, see Define the Component Structure . Write script modules that control component-specific behavior. For more information, see Script Modules . For presentation components, design the layout and appearance of the component. For server pages, this is done using HTML. Create global objects that components can access at runtime, such as messages, variables, and global ProcScript functions. Global objects are defined and deployed in libraries. The information in this section is applicable for all types of applications and components. Detailed information on developing specific types of applications is available in other sections. For more information, see Developing Web Applications and Developing Desktop Applications . Related Links Developing Web Applications You can use Uniface to develop, test, and deploy web-based applications. Web applications have unique requirements with regard to testing and deployment, state management and authentication, data maintenance, and security. Developing Desktop Applications Enterprise desktop applications are distributed client/server applications—they allow users to retrieve and maintain data in a remote database using a locally-run application. Desktop applications are usually highly interactive, and provide a much faster response time than most web applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}